This subnet is providing infrastructure, somewhat like AWS EC2, runpod, vast.ai, and many other web2 and web3 platforms. It's a bit like bricks you can build any building from, but it's not for ordinary people. You usually only use bricks if you are a builder. These "compute horde bricks" are resources especially useful to build AI products on top of them, but actually nothing here says we can only do GPU compute - there is a request from a client already for video processing which will be done on CPUs and we can do other types of resources too.

In bittensor words, sn18 is delivering access to apis such as OpenAI - but ordinary people won't use it. Corcel (a validator) built a (chatgpt-like) product on top of it and that can be used through the browser by the end users.

Integration between sn12 and a validator wanting to monetize it is rather complicated. We provided the documentation for it to every validator that asked + we offered a free middleware for them to start from, which is very easy to integrate. Took the heavy lifting on our shoulders to make it easier for validators to build products on it. Three validator teams are at various stages of integrating it.
